      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"1. REGGIO CALABRIA after having placed in all of his last three runs disappointed last start when finishing 14th of 15 over 1230m at this track when well supported. Trained here and dropping back in distance is worth another chance. 3. PERFECT SISTER is resuming from a spell of five-and-a-half months. Having her first start from the Tom Wolfe stable. Fitter for a sixth in a recent trial over 1000m at Belmont Park and having won fresh-up in the past has definite top-three claims. 2. INSYDE SUCCESS looks close to a winning run after having placed third in all of his last three runs, the latest over 1100m at this track after racing on the speed for most of the trip. Well placed and is worth considering. 4. EL FOXIE resumes from a spell and fresh-up can finish in the money.\",\"runners\":[1,3,2,4],\"exclusive\":true}",
